Builds a `Tree` (nodes + categories) from a slice of `TypedEntry` by rendering each entry's snippet text, grouping variants into single nodes, then delegating to `axis`/`grouping` to bucket leaves and splice in section/axis structure.

`pub fn build(typed: &[TypedEntry], markers: &[Marker], sections: &[Marker], desc_map: &HashMap<usize, String>) -> Result<Tree, String>` is the sole entry point; it runs in two phases — `insert_leaves` (render + dedupe into a flat leaf-only tree, keyed by `tree::group_key`) followed by `group_leaves` (calls `grouping::leaves`, then `axis::group`, then `grouping::apply_grouping` to mutate `tree.node_order`/`nodes`/`categories` in place).

Key non-obvious detail: variants of the same stroke merge into one `Node` via `group_key`, but `one_liner_root` is recomputed separately from `root_segment(&entry.stroke)` — the first `/`-segment of the *raw* stroke, not the grouped key — because it tracks which physical stroke the one-liner's `U` key rides, which `group_key` deliberately discards. If `group_key`'s stripping logic changes, check whether `root_segment` needs to change in step, since they intentionally diverge on the same input.

`BuildState` bundles five mutable refs (`node_order`, `nodes`, `reps`, `categories`, `category_index`) purely to dodge clippy's argument-count lint — not meaningful domain state, just plumbing threaded through `insert_entry`/`insert_all`.

Categories are recorded in first-seen (file) order via `category_index`, deduped by label; `node_order` similarly preserves first-seen order for output stability. Rendering failures from `render_snippet` or `group_key` errors short-circuit the whole build via `?`, surfaced as `Err(String)` — no partial trees are returned on failure. Depends on sibling modules `axis`, `comments::{Marker, label_for}`, `grouping`, and `tree::{Category, Node, Tree, group_key}` — all must stay in sync on the `Node`/`Tree` shape.